SUMMARY
============
This project is my toolset to use portable git.  Use git clone git://github.com/vbjay/Portable-Git.git --recursive to clone the repository.  If you don't have git, 
	Download and run http://www.vbjaysolutions.com/git/PortableGit-netinstall.exe
	Run the Git Bash.vbs script to get a shell to run the tools
	

STEPS to use this project:
============
1.	Download the toolset.
2.	Run the Cleanup.vbs file if you have moved the toolset to another directory.
3.	Run the Git Bash.vbs file to get a git shell and to setup the paths.
4.	Configure the environment by running
		GettingStarted/1stTimesetup.sh
4.	Copy the Git Bash.vbs file to where you want to create or clone the repository.  
5.	Run the Git Bash.vbs file to have a shell at the current directory.
6.	Use Git.

TIPS
============
I have included Git Extensions as a submodule.  To run it just run git ex.